# Vercel v2 (IMA camp) — always deploy

**Rule: Always deploy.** After any change under this repo (`index.html`, `success.html`, `api/`, `package.json`, `vercel.json`), you **must** run a **production** deploy before the task is done. Treat deploy as part of the same turn as the edit.

**Production host:** `ima-summer-camp.vercel.app` and `ima-summer-camp-git-main-tom-richardsons-projects.vercel.app` use Vercel project **`ima-summer-camp`** (not the linked `vercel-v2` folder default). Deploy that project:

```bash
cd /Users/tomrichardson/Downloads/vercel-v2 && VERCEL_ORG_ID=team_PXMrLfQ01zlse3XBsDcaPa3s VERCEL_PROJECT_ID=prj_TJxRFRbKAK4AkYBe8AKL1DoH2k9p npx vercel deploy --prod --yes
```

(Optional second project / alternate alias: `npx vercel --prod --yes` uses linked `vercel-v2` → `vercel-v2-alpha.vercel.app`.)

- Use the **Vercel CLI** for a forced production deploy; do not rely only on git-push auto deploys or tell the user to deploy later.
- If the command fails (auth, network), retry or fix, then deploy again. Only skip if the user **explicitly** says not to deploy.
